# RoboLedger V5.2.19: High-Fidelity Functional Audit

A comprehensive structural and functional upgrade to the V5 interface, bringing it to "Stock Market" levels of dynamic polish while resolving deep-seated parsing and performance issues.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Sequential Ref# System**: I am enabling dynamic Ref# re-sequencing. This means the Ref# (e.g., 001) will always prioritize the top-most row in the current view, updating live as you sort or filter. 
> **Flicker-Free Navigation**: I am switching the Account Switcher from a full-page re-render to a Tabulator-native filter. This will eliminate flickering and hangs, but requires the grid to be fully initialized with all data at once.
> **Adaptive Account Naming**: Switches from `CHQ` -> `CHQ` to a smarter `CHQ1` | `CHQ2` logic with chronological sorting (AMEX -> MC -> CHQ).

## Proposed Changes

### UI Logic (app.js)
- **Scale Expansion**: Increase all `max-width: 1060px` instances to **`1166px`** (+10%).
- **Static Render Prevention**: Re-wire `window.render()` and the Account Switcher to use `txnTable.setFilter()` for account isolation. This prevents the "screen flick" and hanging.
- **Adaptive Naming**: Implement a type-aware label generator for the switcher pills.
- **Pagination**: 
  - Enable Tabulator `pagination: "local"`.
  - Add a footer controls bar with page-size limit dropdown and navigation arrows.
- **Settings Persistence**: Fix [toggleSettings()](file:///g:/My%20Drive/RoboLedger%20-%20NEW/src/ui/enterprise/app.js#181-182) and the save logic to ensure theme (Rainbow default) and density choices are saved to `UI_STATE`.

### Styling (system.css)
- **Structural Dividers**: Add vertical `1px solid rgba(0,0,0,0.06)` lines to grid headers.
- **Dynamic Sorting**: Enable native CSS transitions for Tabulator row movement.
- **Rainbow Default**: Set the Purple-to-Cyan rainbow header as the default theme.
- **COA Tags**: Implement high-fidelity CSS for COA tags (`.coa-tag`) to support the "tickers" update effect.

### Core Logic (ledger.core.js)
- **Parser Polarity Audit**: 
  - Fix `Ingestion.processUpload` to correctly distinguish between debits and credits based on row sign and column headers.
  - Implement a check for negative values in the "Amount" field to correctly set `Polarity.DEBIT`.
- **Sequential Indexing**: Ensure the ledger engine supports live position-based indexing for the Ref# column.

### Session Persistence (V5.2.20)
- **Recovery Logic**: Implement a check on load. If `localStorage` contains transactions, set `UI_STATE.recoveryPending = true`.
- **In-Page Recovery UX**: Add a sleek, V5-styled banner to the top of the Transactions page (in-page, not a popup) if recovery is pending.
  - **Continue**: Dismisses banner and keeps existing data.
  - **Start New**: Triggers `Ledger.reset()`, clears storage, and refreshes the view.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Verification
- **Stress Test**: Switch between accounts rapidly with 1000+ transactions to verify no flicker.
- **Parser Test**: Import a mixed-polarity statement and verify Debit/Credit column distribution.

### Manual Verification
- Verify that "ALL" view shows the combined ledger correctly.
- Confirm Ref# 001 moves to the new top row after a Date sort.
